<subSubSection pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,151,322]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,225,249]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[321,506,226,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mussooriensis">
<emphasis box="[321,506,226,249]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">J. mussooriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[631,752,225,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis box="[631,752,225,249]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">J. malaisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be readily distinguished by the structure of the pygofer and aedeagus. The specimens from Mussoorie were collected on slopes on one side of the path covered with grass and annual herbs belonging to the family 
<taxonomicName box="[681,808,297,321]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
